		"author": "Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi"
	},
	{
		"quote": "This type of interaction keeps at bay the disorganization that solitude brings to the passive mind, but without stimulating much growth. It is rather like a collective form of television watching, and although it is more complex in that it requires participation, its actions and phrases tend to be rigidly scripted and highly predictable.",
		"title": "Flow: The Psychology of Optimal Experience (Harper Perennial Modern Classics)",
