		"author": "John Gottman, Nan Silver"
	},
	{
		"quote": "Then all of a sudden, Olivia puts her hands on her hips and, in perfect imitation of their four-year-old son, sticks out her tongue. Since Nathaniel knows that she’s about to do this, he sticks out his tongue first. Then they both start laughing. As always, this silly contest defuses the tension between them.",
		"title": "The Seven Principles for Making Marriage Work: A Practical Guide from the Country's Foremost Relationship Expert",
		"author": "John Gottman, Nan Silver"
	},
	{
		"quote": "a repair attempt. This term refers to any statement or action—silly or otherwise—that prevents negativity from escalating out of control. Repair attempts are a secret weapon of emotionally intelligent couples—even though many of these couples aren’t aware that they are employing something so powerful. When a couple have a strong friendship, they naturally become experts at sending each other repair attempts and at correctly reading those sent their way.",
