	{
		"quote": "with BPD often don’t have a sense of what they like, what their values are, or who they are.",
		"title": "Loving Someone with Borderline Personality Disorder: How to Keep Out-of-Control Emotions from Destroying Your Relationship",
		"author": "Shari Y. Manning"
	},
	{
		"quote": "one thing that sometimes works is just to give your loved one the time to get those emotions down by holding off on reacting at all for a moment. The woman in my office who heard everything as criticism and got more and more upset no matter what I said finally began to feel her emotions subside when I just got quiet.",
