		"title": "Loving Someone with Borderline Personality Disorder: How to Keep Out-of-Control Emotions from Destroying Your Relationship",
		"author": "Shari Y. Manning"
	},
	{
		"quote": "There is no evidence that regurgitating all of the sadnesses of anyone’s past ever made the person feel better. In fact, doing this can make people with BPD worse and can lead to an increase in suicidal behaviors.",
		"title": "Loving Someone with Borderline Personality Disorder: How to Keep Out-of-Control Emotions from Destroying Your Relationship",
		"author": "Shari Y. Manning"
