		"quote": "It would probably have been much more useful for him and for me if I had used our time together to read aloud to him from books of his choosing, or let him read them silently, with the understanding that whenever he wanted, he could ask me what a word meant and I would tell him—without any questions, explanations, or sound-it-outs.",
		"title": "How Children Fail",
