	{
		"quote": "It is a common assumption that any woman threatened with being raped would do everything in her power to physically resist, Dr. Lisak said, “but it’s not what we find….In fact, most women who are sexually assaulted do not resist. The fear is overwhelming. They often feel helpless. Sometimes they make a conscious choice not to resist because they are afraid if they resist, they will be hurt even worse.” Many victims report afterward to the police that they actually tried “to placate the assailant as a strategy to avoid further harm.”",
